Today marks the 60th anniversary of President John F. Kennedy's assassination, a moment that deeply impacted the nation. Kennedy was known for his leadership on important issues such as civil rights, voting rights, and equal pay for women. He guided the country through the tense moments of the Cold War and inspired the nation to push boundaries, including the mission to the moon. Kennedy's courage, sense of duty, and his family's ability to endure suffering left a lasting impression. His wife, Jacqueline Kennedy, was admired for her grace and resilience during that challenging time. The Kennedys, including Robert and Teddy, have been political heroes and close friends to many. President Kennedy's legacy calls on us to continue striving for an America that lives up to its ideals.